parameters:
\ncUm, sir over there, you have a gloomy expression! If you're
tired of life, w-would you like to come to the Paradise
Church?

\ncIf you have any worries, I will listen and do my best to
help you with anything that's troubling you...!
\nc<>(Oh, it's a fake religion. She's such a cute girl though.)
\nc<>(People are not what they appear to be.)

\nc<>(I should try not to get involved as much as possible...
huh?)

\nc<>Huh, what is it? Are you perhaps drawn to my skillful
missionary work? Are you interested in the Paradise Church?
\nc<>It's not so much skillful as it is suspicious...
\nc<>What is the mark written on that sign?

\nc<>Ah... Is this what you're talking about? It's the emblem of
the Paradise Church! It looks like a secret society, so
it's, um, exciting, right?

\nc<>(No doubt about it. This is the mark that those underlings
of that fake religion had.) (They were secretly carrying
it.)

\nc<>Do you have any bald guys wearing masks at your church? I
think they carry around some strange necklace-like thing...

\nc<>No? There are no suspicious people like that. ...Wait,
that's the villain that appeared the other day, right!?

\nc<>All of our followers, including the founder, are human!
Please don't have any strange suspicions!

\nc<>(So, is it okay then? Villains are beings that come from
another world...)
\nc<>(...No, using the same pattern after all is strange.)

\nc<>(This child might be lying,)
(There is also a
possibility that they are being deceived by the villain.)

\nc<>Well, if you understand, that's good. Geez, it's really
troublesome with all these prejudices.

\nc<>But everyone here is really nice, so if you have anything
you want to talk about, please feel free to contact us
anytime.
\nc<>W-We won't abandon the troubled little lambs!

\nc<>For now, let's keep it. It's best to get close to the other
party for investigation purposes.
\nc<>I obtained the memory N1: Suspicious Religion.

\nc<>Sigh~ I got fired from my part-time job again. Well, it's
only natural since I just walked out in the middle of work.
